Choodha Vadhai Ceremony ❤️

"From the time I was a little girl, I've always been captivated by weddings and the excitement that surrounds them. But for me, it was the Choora that held a special place in my heart. I used to dream about the day I would get to wear one, and as I grew older, it became one of the things I most looked forward to about getting married.

And now, as I stand here wearing my Choora, I can say with certainty that it was worth every bit of the excitement and anticipation. It's amazing how something as simple as a set of bangles can hold so much meaning and tradition, and I feel incredibly lucky to be a part of it. Thats why i wore it for almost 2.5 years . 

To all the little girls out there dreaming about their own Choora, hold onto that dream - it just might come true one day. And to all the brides-to-be out there, cherish every moment of this special time in your life. It's a once-in-a-lifetime experience that you'll never forget.

Thankyou @madhukathuria for making me feel special in every way possible trust me i have the best Mother in law in the world 🧿

 #ChooraWadhai #ChildhoodDreams #marriedlife
